[?2004l[?2004h> # Scheduler App DST Bug Fix
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Problem
[?2004l[?2004h> The scheduler app was sending meeting reminders at incorrect times for meetings between 2am-3am local time (Europe/Berlin), with exactly 1 hour offset. This occurred specifically during DST transitions.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Root Cause
[?2004l[?2004h> In `app.py`, the `convert_to_berlin()` function had a critical bug:
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> # BUGGY CODE (line 27):
[?2004l[?2004h> utc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')
[?2004l[?2004h> berlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)  # WRONG!
[?2004l[?2004h> ```
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> The bug: `BERLIN_TZ.localize()` was treating the naive UTC datetime as if it were already in Berlin time, instead of converting FROM UTC TO Berlin.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Solution
[?2004l[?2004h> Fixed the conversion to properly handle timezone-aware datetime objects:
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> # FIXED CODE:
[?2004l[?2004h> utc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')
[?2004l[?2004h> utc_dt = UTC_TZ.localize(utc_dt)        # Make it UTC-aware first
[?2004l[?2004h> berlin_dt = utc_dt.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)  # Then convert to Berlin
[?2004l[?2004h> ```
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Impact
[?2004l[?2004h> - The Monday 2:30am maintenance window meeting (stored as 2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC) now correctly converts to 03:30 CEST instead of 01:30 CET
[?2004l[?2004h> - During DST transition on March 31, 2024, when clocks spring forward from 2am to 3am, the conversion now properly accounts for this
[?2004l[?2004h> - All timezone conversions now work correctly regardless of DST status
[?2004l[?2004h> 
